🗄️ Common Database Default Ports
Database	Default Port	Notes
MySQL	    3306	Most widely used relational DB
MariaDB	    3306	MySQL-compatible
PostgreSQL	5432	Popular in modern backend systems
MongoDB	    27017	NoSQL (document-based)
Redis	    6379	In-memory cache / key-value store
Oracle DB	1521	Enterprise database
Microsoft	1433	Used in Windows ecosystems
SQL Server
SQLite	❌  N/A	File-based (no port)
Cassandra	9042	NoSQL wide-column store
CouchDB	    5984	HTTP-based NoSQL
Neo4j	    7687	Bolt protocol (graph DB)
Elasticsearch	9200	REST API
Elasticsearch (cluster)	9300	Node-to-node communication
DynamoDB (local)	8000	AWS local testing
HBase	    16000	Master server
HBase RegionServer	16020	Region node
InfluxDB	8086	Time-series DB
Memcached	11211	Cache (not persistent DB)
RabbitMQ (queue) 5672	Messaging (not DB, but used like one sometimes)